{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Customer Churn Prediction - Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook performs initial exploratory data analysis on the customer churn dataset to understand the data structure, identify patterns, and uncover insights that will inform our modeling approach."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import necessary libraries\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style for better visualizations\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display settings\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.width', None)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data Loading and Initial Exploration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load the dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data/customer_churn.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display basic information about the dataset\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nColumn names:\\n{df.columns.tolist()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Convert TotalCharges to numeric, handling empty strings\n",
    "df['TotalCharges'] = pd.to_numeric(df['TotalCharges'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill NaN values with 0 (these are likely new customers with no charges yet)\n",
    "df['TotalCharges'] = df['TotalCharges'].fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check for missing values\n",
    "print(f\"Missing values after conversion:\\n{df.isnull().sum()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display first few rows\n",
    "print(\"First 5 rows of the dataset:\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display basic statistics\n",
    "print(\"Basic statistics for numerical columns:\")\n",
    "df.describe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Display data types\n",
    "print(\"Data types:\")\n",
    "df.dtypes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Findings: Data Loading and Initial Exploration\n",
    "\n",
    "- The dataset contains 7,043 customers with 21 features\n",
    "- `TotalCharges` had 11 missing values that were successfully converted to numeric and filled with 0\n",
    "- The dataset includes a mix of numerical (tenure, MonthlyCharges, TotalCharges) and categorical features\n",
    `- `customerID` appears to be a unique identifier and can be excluded from modeling\n",
    "- `SeniorCitizen` is stored as integer (0/1) but represents a categorical variable"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Target Variable Analysis - Churn Distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Plot churn distribution\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "ax = sns.countplot(data=df, x='Churn')\n",
    "plt.title('Customer Churn Distribution', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Churn', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=12)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add percentage labels on bars\n",
    "total = len(df)\n",
    "for p in ax.patches:\n",
    "    percentage = f'{100 * p.get_height() / total:.1f}%'\n",
    "    x = p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2\n",
    "    y = p.get_height()\n",
    "    ax.annotate(percentage, (x, y), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print exact counts and percentages\n",
    "churn_counts = df['Churn'].value_counts()\n",
    "churn_percentages = df['Churn'].value_counts(normalize=True) * 100\n",
    "print(\"Churn Distribution:\")\n",
    "for status in churn_counts.index:\n",
    "    print(f\"{status}: {churn_counts[status]} ({churn_percentages[status]:.1f}%)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Findings: Churn Distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Class imbalance detected**: 26.6% of customers have churned (1,869 out of 7,043)\n",
    "- 73.4% of customers remain active (5,174 out of 7,043)\n",
    "- This imbalance will need to be addressed during modeling (e.g., using class weights, SMOTE, or appropriate evaluation metrics)\n",
    "- The churn rate of 26.6% is relatively high, indicating a significant business problem to address"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Numerical Features Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create histograms for numerical features\n",
    "numerical_features = ['tenure', 'MonthlyCharges', 'TotalCharges']\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Distribution of Numerical Features', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, feature in enumerate(numerical_features):\n",
    "    sns.histplot(data=df, x=feature, kde=True, ax=axes[i])\n",
    "    axes[i].set_title(f'{feature} Distribution', fontsize=14)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_xlabel(feature, fontsize=12)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=12)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create box plots to show distribution by churn status\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Numerical Features by Churn Status', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, feature in enumerate(numerical_features):\n",
    "    sns.boxplot(data=df, x='Churn', y=feature, ax=axes[i])\n",
    "    axes[i].set_title(f'{feature} by Churn', fontsize=14)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_xlabel('Churn', fontsize=12)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_ylabel(feature, fontsize=12)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Findings: Numerical Features Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tenure:**\n",
    "- Bimodal distribution with peaks at very new customers (0-2 months) and long-term customers (70+ months)\n",
    "- Customers who churn tend to have significantly lower tenure (median ~10 months vs 38 months for non-churners)\n",
    "- New customers are much more likely to churn\n",
    "\n",
    "**MonthlyCharges:**\n",
    "- Multi-modal distribution suggesting different service tiers\n",
    "- Customers who churn have higher monthly charges (median ~$80 vs $65 for non-churners)\n",
    "- Higher monthly charges appear to be a risk factor for churn\n",
    "\n",
    "**TotalCharges:**\n",
    "- Right-skewed distribution due to relationship with tenure\n",
    "- Customers who churn have lower total charges (expected due to shorter tenure)\n",
    "- This feature is highly correlated with tenure and monthly charges"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Categorical Features Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Analyze key categorical features vs churn\n",
    "categorical_features = ['Contract', 'InternetService', 'TechSupport']\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 6))\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Categorical Features vs Churn', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, feature in enumerate(categorical_features):\n",
    "    # Create count plot\n",
    "    sns.countplot(data=df, x=feature, hue='Churn', ax=axes[i])\n",
    "    axes[i].set_title(f'{feature} by Churn Status', fontsize=14)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_xlabel(feature, fontsize=12)\n",
    "    axes[i].set_ylabel('Count', fontsize=12)\n",
    "    axes[i].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add legend only to first subplot\n",
    "    if i == 0:\n",
    "        axes[i].legend(title='Churn')\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        axes[i].get_legend().remove()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate churn rates by category\n",
    "for feature in categorical_features:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nChurn rate by {feature}:\")\n",
    "    churn_rate = df.groupby(feature)['Churn'].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack()['Yes'] * 100\n",
    "    print(churn_rate.round(1))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Findings: Categorical Features Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**Contract Type:**\n",
    "- Month-to-month contracts have the highest churn rate (42.7%)\n",
    "- One-year contracts show moderate churn (11.3%)\n",
    "- Two-year contracts have the lowest churn rate (2.8%)\n",
    "- Contract length is a strong predictor of churn\n",
    "\n",
    "**Internet Service:**\n",
    "- Fiber optic customers have the highest churn rate (41.9%)\n",
    "- DSL customers have moderate churn (19.0%)\n",
    "- Customers without internet service have very low churn (7.4%)\n",
    "- Fiber optic service may have quality or pricing issues\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tech Support:**\n",
    "- Customers without tech support have high churn rate (41.6%)\n",
    "- Customers with tech support have much lower churn (15.2%)\n",
    "- No internet service customers have very low churn (7.4%)\n",
    "- Tech support appears to be a significant retention factor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Correlation Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Select only numerical columns for correlation\n",
    "numerical_df = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate correlation matrix\n",
    "correlation_matrix = numerical_df.corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create heatmap\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', center=0, \n",
    "            square=True, fmt='.2f', cbar_kws={'shrink': 0.8})\n",
    "plt.title('Correlation Matrix of Numerical Features', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Print correlation values with target (if we encode churn as binary)\n",
    "df_encoded = df.copy()\n",
    "df_encoded['Churn_binary'] = (df_encoded['Churn'] == 'Yes').astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Correlations with churn\n",
    "correlations_with_churn = numerical_df.corrwith(df_encoded['Churn_binary'])\n",
    "print(\"Correlations with Churn:\")\n",
    "print(correlations_with_churn.round(3).sort_values(ascending=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Findings: Correlation Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Correlations:**\n",
    "- `TotalCharges` and `tenure` are strongly correlated (0.83) - expected as longer tenure leads to higher total charges\n",
    "- `TotalCharges` and `MonthlyCharges` are moderately correlated (0.65)\n",
    "- `tenure` and `MonthlyCharges` have weak positive correlation (0.25)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Correlations with Churn:**\n",
    - `tenure` shows negative correlation with churn (-0.35) - longer tenure reduces churn risk\n",
    "- `MonthlyCharges` shows positive correlation with churn (0.19) - higher monthly charges increase churn risk\n",
    "- `TotalCharges` shows negative correlation with churn (-0.20) - likely due to tenure effect\n",
    "\n",
    "**Implications:**\n",
    "- High correlation between `tenure` and `TotalCharges` suggests potential multicollinearity\n",
    "- Consider feature engineering or dimensionality reduction techniques\n",
    "- `tenure` appears to be the strongest numerical predictor of churn"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Summary and Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Insights:\n",
    "1. **Class Imbalance**: 26.6% churn rate requires careful handling in modeling\n",
    "2. **Strong Predictors**: Contract type, tenure, and tech support are powerful churn indicators\n",
    "3. **Risk Factors**: Month-to-month contracts, high monthly charges, and no tech support increase churn risk\n",
    "4. **Retention Factors**: Long-term contracts, tech support, and longer tenure reduce churn\n",
    "\n",
    "### Recommendations for Modeling:\n",
    "1. Handle class imbalance using appropriate techniques (SMOTE, class weights)\n",
    "2. Consider feature engineering for tenure-based segments\n",
    "3. Address multicollinearity between tenure and TotalCharges\n",
    "4. Use appropriate evaluation metrics (F1-score, AUC-ROC) due to class imbalance\n",
    "5. Consider tree-based models that can handle mixed data types well\n",
    "\n",
    "### Data Quality Issues Resolved:\n",
    "- Converted `TotalCharges` to numeric and handled missing values\n",
    "- Identified `SeniorCitizen` as categorical despite numeric storage\n",
    "- Confirmed data integrity after preprocessing"
   ]
  }
 ],
